703916f-a.text:
Cumberland Street, east side, south rom (No. 101) a point midway between Park and Myrtle Avenues, looking toward the latter. The auto parking space is the former site of the Brooklyn Cancer Institute. View 2 is south across the Myrtle Avenue elevated trestle. These buildings were later demolished anc the site made part of Fort Greene Houses, a 1ow-rent city housing center.
October 10, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
